transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir. How are you?

Speaker 1: I'm doing well. How about you, sir?

Speaker 2: My name is Ali Mehtar.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: They send me to Niagara every month, and I'm moving this month.

Speaker 1: Okay. You need to skip this month?

Speaker 2: Huh?

Speaker 1: You want to skip the month?

Speaker 2: Yeah. I don't know how long it's going to take, but I'll skip it because I'm going overseas.

Speaker 1: When I come back, I'll call you.

Speaker 2: Okay. So you want me to stop it entirely?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay. What's your zip code, sir?

Speaker 1: 44333.

Speaker 2: Okay. And just so I can note it, you're moving and going out of the country for a while. That's why?

Speaker 1: What is it?

Speaker 2: Just so I can note in your account why I stopped it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: You're going out of the country for a while?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay. I just want to make sure I heard you right. Okay. We're all set. Ridgewood Road, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay. We're good to go.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah. We're set.

Speaker 1: When I come back, I call you on the same number I call you now?

Speaker 2: Yeah. Yeah. Call the same number, and I put a note in here that you're just leaving the country,

Speaker 1: and you're not sure when you're going to be back, so you'll call back.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thanks. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.
